Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Cut the @baguette{1} into 1-inch cubes. Peel and cut the @rainbow carrots{1%bunch} into 3-inch pieces, halving or quartering any wider pieces. Strip the @rosemary{1%sprig} leaves from the sprig, then finely chop.

Arrange the croutons and carrots on separate sides of a #baking sheet{} and drizzle each with @olive oil{1/2%tbsp}, the chopped rosemary, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Lightly toss, then place in the oven for ~{10-12%minutes}, until croutons are toasted. Remove the baking sheet from the oven and set croutons aside. Return the baking sheet to oven and allow the carrots to cook for ~{10-15%minutes} more, until caramelized and tender.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @shallot{1} and @garlic{2%cloves}. Remove and discard the ribs and stems from the @Tuscan kale{1%bunch} and thinly slice the leaves. Cut the @fresh mozzarella{6%ounce} into 1/2-inch cubes. Zest and juice the @lemon{1}.

Toss the mozzarella in a large #bowl{} with @herbes de Provence{1%tsp}, @lemon zest{1/2%tsp}, @lemon juice{1%tbsp}, and @olive oil{1%tbsp}.

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the shallot and cook, tossing, for ~{5%minutes} or until soft. Add the kale to the pan and toss until wilted, about ~{4%minutes}, adding a splash of water if necessary. Add the garlic to the pan and cook for another ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and set aside.

Once the carrots are ready, stir them into the bowl with marinated mozzarella along with the kale and croutons. Season with salt and pepper.

> Panzanella is a traditional Italian bread salad. We put a twist on the classic recipe that uses tomatoes, by adding vitamin-rich kale and sweet roasted carrots. Creamy fresh mozzarella was too good to pass up, so we decided to amp it up with some herbs de Provence. Mamma would be proud!